Source:  Off the Sheep's Back
Author:  RICHARDS
Vol / Page:  56
Edition:
Quote:  Because my left arm was often numb and useless, I developed a style of holding the sheep entirely wih my legs, keeping it on the point of `balance'. Many years later, with certain modifications, this style became known as the `Bowen technique', and has been taught throughout the world.
